Shanghai is currently experiencing its worst COVID-19 outbreak. The megacity reports hundreds of confirmed locally transmitted cases and thousands of asymptomatic carriers every day. Authorities have implemented the lockdown in two phases from March 28 to April 5, first targeting the eastern part of the Huangpu River, followed by the west. Wang Wenya is a CGTN stringer who is under lockdown in Shanghai due to the rise in COVID-19 cases. In this video, she shares her experience â€“ from receiving supplies for antigen testing to online meetings.